title: Soft Skill Trainer
tagsAndSkills: Soft Skills Training,Training Analysis,Behavioural Training,Behavioral Training,Language Training,Training Delivery,Soft skills,Delivery
jobDescription:
Training Design and Development:

Create and update training materials, including manuals, presentations, and interactive content, tailored to the needs of call center staff.

Develop and implement training programs focused on soft skills such as communication, empathy, conflict resolution, and active listening.

Training Delivery:

Conduct engaging training sessions and workshops for call center agents, ensuring content is relevant and actionable.

Utilize various training methods, including role-playing, simulations, and group discussions, to enhance learning and retention.

Assessment and Feedback:

Evaluate the effectiveness of training programs through assessments, feedback surveys, and performance metrics.

Provide constructive feedback and coaching to employees to support their development and improve performance.

Collaboration and Support:

Work closely with call center management to identify training needs and customize programs accordingly.

Support new hire onboarding by delivering initial soft skills training and integrating new employees into the team.

Continuous Improvement:

Stay updated on industry best practices and emerging trends in call center operations and soft skills training.

Continuously assess and refine training programs to ensure they meet the evolving needs of the organization.
